"title": "6615: atonement, necessity and nature of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6615: atonement, necessity and nature of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Scripture stresses the seriousness and reality of human sin, and that human beings are unable to atone for their own sins. In his grace, God provides a means by which the situation can be remedied.</p>\n<h2>Atonement is necessary because of human sinfulness</h2>\n<h3>Atonement is necessary because sin cuts people off from God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:2\">ISA 59:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa64:7\">ISA 64:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek39:23\">EZK 39:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab1:13\">HAB 1:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:31\">JHN 9:31</a></p>\n<h3>Atonement is necessary because sin provokes God's wrath</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:1-Eph2:3\">EPH 2:1–2:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:5-Gen6:7\">GEN 6:5–6:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:30-Exod32:35\">EXO 32:30–32:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:18-Rom1:20\">ROM 1:18–1:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:8\">ROM 2:8</a></p>\n<h2>God's gracious nature is the basis for atonement</h2>\n<h3>Atonement is grounded in God's reluctance to punish sinners</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:32\">EZK 18:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek33:11\">EZK 33:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:1-1Tim2:4\">1TI 2:1–2:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:9\">2PE 3:9</a></p>\n<h3>Atonement is grounded in God's readiness to forgive sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:6-Exod34:7\">EXO 34:6–34:7</a></strong> <em>The punishment of subsequent generations makes God's abhorrence of sin quite clear, but the extension of his love and forgiveness “to thousands” puts the emphasis in these verses on God's grace and compassion.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps145:8\">PSA 145:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:9\">DAN 9:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah4:2\">JON 4:2</a></p>\n<h3>Atonement is grounded in God's covenant love</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:19\">NUM 14:19</a></strong> <em>The Hebrew word for “great love” means God's loving faithfulness to those within the covenant.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps25:6-Ps25:7\">PSA 25:6–25:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps103:8-Ps103:12\">PSA 103:8–103:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:13\">JOL 2:13</a></p>\n<h2>God's provision of atonement is a means of dealing with sin</h2>\n<h3>Atonement through sacrifice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev9:7\">LEV 9:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:10\">EXO 30:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:22-Num15:26\">NUM 15:22–15:26</a></p>\n<h3>God's promised new covenant of forgiveness was fulfilled in Jesus Christ's atoning death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:16-Heb10:17\">HEB 10:16–10:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:33-Jer31:34\">JER 31:33–31:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:28\">MAT 26:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:15\">HEB 9:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:24\">HEB 12:24</a></p>\n<h2>Images used to portray the at-one-ment, or restored relationship, between God and humanity</h2>\n<h3>Atonement as forgiveness of sins</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:7-Eph1:8\">EPH 1:7–1:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:22\">LEV 19:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:38\">ACT 13:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:13-Col2:14\">COL 2:13–2:14</a></p>\n<h3>Atonement as cleansing and purification</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:30\">LEV 16:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:6-Isa6:7\">ISA 6:6–6:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:14\">TIT 2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:7\">1JN 1:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:14\">REV 7:14</a></p>\n<h3>Atonement as reconciliation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:19\">2CO 5:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:9-Rom5:11\">ROM 5:9–5:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:14-Eph2:16\">EPH 2:14–2:16</a></p>\n<h3>Atonement as healing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:24\">1PE 2:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:14\">2CH 7:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps103:2-Ps103:3\">PSA 103:2–103:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:5\">ISA 53:5</a></p>\n<h3>Atonement as God buying people back for himself</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:9\">REV 5:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:28\">MAT 20:28</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:45\">MRK 10:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:28\">ACT 20:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:18-1Pet1:19\">1PE 1:18–1:19</a></p>\n<h3>Atonement as making holy: creating a relationship of consecrated nearness to God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:10\">HEB 10:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:22\">COL 1:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:12\">HEB 13:12</a></p>",
